  "texts": [
    "This review highlights significant growth in the application of DL methodologies to paleontological problems since 2017, with the most rapid advancements occurring in the past three years.",
    "The application of DL for fossil classification is more common than its application to segmentation tasks, but there is significant potential in both areas for future exploration.",
    "In particular, the application of DL to the classification of microfossils is poised to greatly enhance the speed of analysis and thus data volumes, offering substantial benefits for biostratigraphy and paleoenvironmental reconstruction.",
    "Furthermore, we have introduced innovative approaches-adapted from advancements in other disciplines-that have the potential to further enrich paleontological studies.",
    "These include sophisticated techniques for image augmentation, state-of-the-art image enhancement methods, and the development of novel neural network architectures."
